nit: `string_view` can be used, as it is read-only access to a string and can avoid unnecessary memory allocation and copying.
In this case, you also would need to do:

```diff
static RPCHelpMan setwalletflag()
{
            std::string flags;
            for (auto& it : STRING_TO_WALLET_FLAG)
                if (it.second & MUTABLE_WALLET_FLAGS)
-                    flags += (flags == "" ? "" : ", ") + it.first;             
+                    flags += (flags == "" ? "" : ", ") + std::string(it.first);
```

